  "body": "<!-- **Are you in the right place?**\r\n1. For issues or feature requests, please create an issue in this repository.\r\n2. For general technical and non-technical questions, we are happy to help you on our [Rook.io Slack](https://Rook-io.slack.com).\r\n3. Did you already search the existing open issues for anything similar? -->\r\n\r\n**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Feature Request\r\n\r\nBoth EdgeFS and Ceph Rook operators will benefit from generic API to enable multi-homed network via existing Kubernetes solutions. One of them is https://github.com/intel/multus-cni.\r\n\r\n**What should the feature do:**\r\n\r\nProvide generic Rook API that would be called by EdgeFS and Ceph operators to enable multi-homed cluster namespaces.\r\n\r\n**What is use case behind this feature:**\r\n\r\nWe'd like to solve most critical issue of client vs backend network separation. Kubernetes's simplistic flat model only good enough for limited use cases. Production environments often need strong isolation in terms of to reduce tail latency, improve QoS/SLA and data security.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n<!-- Specific environment information that helps with the feature request -->\r\n",
